overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and an existing Statement of
  Work. The primary goal was to ensure all acceptance criteria were met and to
  implement any identified missing features. The agent conducted a thorough
  review, identifying several critical gaps. Subsequently, the agent proceeded
  to implement these missing features. Key implementations included adding a
  1-10 severity scale for tiredness with associated safety warnings, integrating
  detection and reporting for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, incorporating placeholder outbound links to
  various sleep and mental health resources, and implementing a weighted scoring
  system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS). Furthermore, the CSV export
  functionality was expanded to include all questionnaire response data, and new
  questions were added to screen for pain severity and chronic fatigue symptoms.
  The agent systematically updated relevant TypeScript types, Zod validation
  schemas, React components for the questionnaire UI, and both the HTML and PDF
  report generation logic to reflect these new features and calculations.
